Reasoning: The paper investigates the contribution made by masses in Q&A portals, specifically in StackOverflow. This involves analyzing user behavior and the impact of their contributions on the system. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
